=> JWT(JSON Web Token) Authentication

  -> Without JWT 
  	
  	-  Without JWT we don't have advanced features like expiration Time
  	-  Can be decoded Easily
  	-  Should we go for "Custom Token System", so that user need not share username and password each time
  	-  JSON Web Tokens are an oen and industry standard
  	-  User tries to login , once user is authenticated , Token is issued to user
  	-  With Every request Token sent in API requests, Request authorized if valid, else error
  
  -> How is Token sent
  
  	- Token is sent using HTTP Authorization header
  	- format : Bearer <token>
  	- token consist of Header(algorithm+type will be jwt)+payload+signature encoded info
  	- Algorithm is for signature
  	
  	- We will be creating Below classes
  	
  		- JwtUtils
  		- AuthTokenFilter
  		- AuthEntryPointJwt
  		- SecurityConfig - we will update
  		
  	- JwtUtils
  	
  		- JwtUtils class mainly contains utility methods for generating, parsing and validating JWTs
  		- Include generating a token from username, Validating a JWT token and extracting the token from username
  	
  	- AuthTokenFilter extends abstract class OncePerRequestFilter which has method doFilterInternal
  	
  		- Filter incoming requests to check for a valid JWT in the header, setting the authentication context if the token is valid
  		- Extracts JWT token from request, validates it and configure the spring security context with user details if token is valid
  		
  	- AuthEntryPointJwt
  	
  		-  provides custom handling for unauthorized requests, typically when authentication is required but not supplied or valid
  		- when an unauthorized request is detected, it logs the error and returns JSON response with error message,status code and path attempted.
  		
  	-  SecurityConfig
  	
  		- configures spring security filters and rules for application
  		- Sets up the security filter chain, permitting or denying access based paths and roles.
  		- It also configures session management to stateless, which is crucial for JWT usage
  		
  	- Dependencies -> https://github.com/jwtk/jjwt?tab=readme-ov-file#maven

  	
  	